===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Dougherty had a population of 62, with 34 households and 26 families residing in the city.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A22080&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A22080&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref> The [[population density]] was 110.6 inhabitants per square mile (42.7/km<sup>2</sup>). The median age was 45.8 years. 25.8% of residents were under the age of 18 and 16.1% were 65 years of age or older. For every 100 females there were 138.5 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over there were 130.0 males age 18 and over. The gender makeup of the city was 58.1% male and 41.9% female.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A22080&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

There were 34 households, of which 50.0% had children under the age of 18 living in them. Of all households, 52.9% were married-couple households, 11.8% were cohabitating-couple households, 35.3% were households with a male householder and no spouse or partner present, and 0.0% were households with a female householder and no spouse or partner present. Non-families made up 23.5% of households. About 17.6% of all households were made up of individuals and 5.9% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

There were 38 housing units at an average density of 67.8 per square mile (26.2/km<sup>2</sup>), of which 10.5% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

